caption.text:
@bg2fast‘s (BG2FAST) take on football hits different 🏈  The creator began making videos about different catches and routes after no longer being able to play professionally. “I love that I can still compete, create and express myself through football — turn creativity into something that inspires millions.” ⁣
 And wearing @oakleymeta Vanguard AI glasses brings a more authentic, first-person and hands-free vibe to every play. 😎

caption.text:
The streets of Mumbai are @diyajoukani’s (Diya Joukani) runway ✨⁣
⁣
When the clothes Diya wanted to wear didn’t exist, she decided to make her own. The fashion designer has gone viral, showcasing her looks while doing everyday activities in her home city, like walking a goat or getting fruit from a stand.⁣
⁣
“My designs are living memories of ancient traditional embroidery techniques. I wear them and film myself while I’m going to and from my studio and fabric markets.” ⁣
⁣
Video by @diyajoukani

caption.text:
New vision board hack 🔓⁣
⁣
Internet artist @emmaorhun (Emma Orhun) is done leaving her goals up to chance and decided to visualize them with a mix of digital and analog assets — including text that she restyled using @meta.ai (Meta AI) in Stories.⁣
⁣
“I like to take electronic assets and bring them into the real world using physical materials. It’s about finding one point of similarity between them and then connecting the rest of the dots from there.” ⁣
⁣
Watch to see Emma’s final product, which she describes as “playful, earnest and scrappy.” 🖼️✨💭⁣
 ⁣
Video by @emmaorhun
